INSERT INTO `cm_article` VALUES ('8a3321b63f26cfbb013f32f7cb82014f', '', 'Wireframing Tools for Mobile', 'Proto, Moqups, UXPin, Balsamiq, Justinmind, Fluid', '<ul class=\"slides\" style=\"padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; list-style: none; color: rgb(85, 85, 85); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">1.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://proto.io/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Proto</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Proto\" src=\"http://rack.3.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxLzM0L3Byb3RvLjdkODI5LmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTg1MHg1OTA-CmUJanBn/b7be84cb/9c7/proto.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Proto.io is a dedicated mobile prototyping platform to build and deploy fully interactive mobile app prototypes and simulations that resemble the finished product. It runs in most web browsers and features three main interfaces: dashboard, editor and the player. The dashboard is the interface where you manage projects. The editor is the building environment that comes with a set of tools to design and develop the prototypes and build interactions. The player is used for viewing and interacting with the prototype and offers tools for annotating and leaving feedback.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">You can test your prototype directly on real mobile devices, and run it in full screen mode using (free) browser apps for both iOS or Android devices.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">2.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://moqups.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Moqups</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Moqups\" src=\"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxLzE5L21vcXVwcy4xYWI5Ni5qcGcKcAl0aHVtYgk4NTB4NTkwPgplCWpwZw/87f2b031/3cb/moqups.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Moqups is a nifty, free HTML5 app to create wireframes, mockups or UI concepts with a lovingly crafted, unpretentious interface. It\'s simple to use and has pre-built stencils so you can get started straight away, including radio buttons, links, image placeholders, text boxes, sliders and much more.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">There are iPhone and iPad templates, along with iOS buttons, alerts, pickers, menus, segments, switches and a keyboard. You can set the size of the grid and preview and share your wireframes. The most useful feature is snap to grid, which allows for perfect alignment of objects.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">3.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://uxpin.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">UXPin</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Uxpin\" src=\"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxLzFiL3V4cGluLjc1M2JmLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTg1MHg1OTA-CmUJanBn/40571fad/75f/uxpin.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">UXPin is a quick and easy tool for creating mockups and on-line clickable prototypes. After purchasing&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.justproto.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">JustProto</a>, the company used it as the backbone for UXPin.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Built on solid user experience design principles, it offers a full toolkit of good user design patterns and elements to build a great design from the ground up. With the responsive breakpoints, create responsive prototypes and wireframes that will work on various devices and resolutions. It features version control and iterations with easily shareable previews, intuitive commenting and real-time collaborative editing and chat.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">It boasts a huge library of attractive user interface elements styled for the web, iOS, Android and more, with a quick, responsive drag and drop interface.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">4.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.balsamiq.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Balsamiq</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Balsamiq\" src=\"http://rack.0.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxL2FhL2JhbHNhbWlxLjc2M2Q5LmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTg1MHg1OTA-CmUJanBn/f7063574/937/balsamiq.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Balsamiq Mockups is a rapid wireframing tool that lets you generate ideas quickly. It reproduces the experience of sketching on a whiteboard, which allows easy sharing, collaboration and feedback. With over 75 built-in interface components and 187 icons, plus a host of community generated components, there is no shortage of ready-to-use objects and elements.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Access a wealth of components for mobile wireframing with the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://mockupstogo.mybalsamiq.com/projects\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Mockups To Go</a>&nbsp;library, which showcases downloadable pre-made templates for Android, Blackberry and iOS. You can share and present your mockups or utilize \"linking,\" which lets you generate click-through prototypes for demos and usability testing.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">5.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.justinmind.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Justinmind</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Justinmind\" src=\"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxLzBkL2p1c3Rpbm1pbmQuZTI1YjQuanBnCnAJdGh1bWIJODUweDU5MD4KZQlqcGc/5ae4f9ba/db8/justinmind.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">A platform for creating rich, interactive web and mobile wireframes, Justinmind includes iPhone, Android and iPad gestures such as swipe, tap-and-hold, pinch and rotate, which can be included in your mobile wireframe to create a fully interactive prototype. Of particular interest is the \"simulate\" feature: If you change your wireframe, Justinmind will simulate your application prototype instantly.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">The ability to create customized widgets and group them into widget libraries is useful, with a wide range of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.justinmind.com/prototyper/widgets-web\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">widget libraries</a>&nbsp;available for iPhone, iPad, Blackberry, Android and others.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">6.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.fluidui.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Fluid</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Fluidui\" src=\"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxL2E3L2ZsdWlkdWkuZjNkZWMuanBnCnAJdGh1bWIJODUweDU5MD4KZQlqcGc/d844a0b6/c45/fluidui.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">An HTML5, browser-based app for creating interactive prototypes and wireframes of Android, iOS and Windows 8 apps, FluidUI features a drag-and-drop interface boasting gestures, mobile-style animations and transitions and visual linking for testing and demos. With over 1,700 ready-made wireframe and phone UI elements, which are updated often, there is a vast number of resources to get started quickly.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">You can preview mockups as you design using the Fluid Player for instant feedback, and share and publish your project, with export available as PNG images, a PDF or an HTML5 preview.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">7.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.axure.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Axure</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Axure\" src=\"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxLzJjL2F4dXJlLjZhZDUwLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTg1MHg1OTA-CmUJanBn/37e0dafb/dd3/axure.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">With Axure you can generate interactive HTML wireframes and UI mockups with the simple drag-and-drop interface, which makes it easy to lay out interfaces, edit content and add interactivity to your mobile mockup.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">The extensive elements library, with shapes, widgets and panels along with buttons and popup windows (and more), can be used to create an interactive prototype. The smart conditional logic can help craft realistic user flows like logins, and the swipe interactions are particularly useful. There are also&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.axure.com/download-widget-libraries\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">downloadable widget libraries</a>&nbsp;to use in your projects, including iOS wireframes, Retina widgets, iPhone UI elements, iPad library, Android library and more.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">You can upload the finished wireframe to your own web server and navigate to it on your phone for testing. You can use Axure to create mockups for Android, iPad, iPhone and mobile websites, with UI elements specifically built for each device.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">8.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.mockflow.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Mockflow</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Mockflow\" src=\"http://rack.3.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxLzBlL21vY2tmbG93LmQwMTUxLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTg1MHg1OTA-CmUJanBn/44e2614f/f6b/mockflow.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Offering fast, efficient wireframing for websites and mobile apps, Mockflow offers an easy-to-use, sophisticated interface with a presentation mode to test wireframe interactions, along with graphs, grids and rulers to craft a well-planned interface. The vast library of wireframe components is impressive; you have a choice of four templates to use immediately (iPhone app, Android app, iPad app and Windows Phone) or you can choose to start from scratch with your own layout. Download other elements and templates from the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.mockflow.com/mockstore/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">MockStore</a>.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Mockflow encourages collaboration with a chat feature, and co-editors of a project can make changes at the same time, but on different pages to avoid conflicts. Export projects in a variety of formats and view them on mobile devices and tablets to thoroughly test their functionality.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">9.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.protoshare.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Protoshare</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Protoshare\" src=\"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxLzY5L3Byb3Rvc2hhcmUuODAzMzkuanBnCnAJdGh1bWIJODUweDU5MD4KZQlqcGc/adb50673/892/protoshare.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">A powerful wireframe and prototyping platform, Protoshare offers an extensive mobile toolset with pre-configured mobile screen guides, mobile stencils from a central resource library, and 2D and 3D animated transitions. You can quickly create interactive wireframes and mobile prototypes with the drag-and-drop interface, then send to an iPhone, iPad or Android mobile device to test and experience how the app functions. Teams can share feedback in the Review interface and respond to discussions, and project members can mark and track decisions based on that feedback.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">The resource library means you can quickly build your mobile wireframes with stencils, garner feedback and evolve the wireframes to higher fidelity prototypes.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">10.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wireframe.cc/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Wireframe</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Wireframe\" src=\"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxLzQxL3dpcmVmcmFtZS4yM2FhYy5qcGcKcAl0aHVtYgk4NTB4NTkwPgplCWpwZw/8db17809/d1e/wireframe.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Wireframe is a super simple tool for creating wireframes with a \"click and drag to draw\" interface. Editing is done via a double-click, and the minimal interface means a clutter-free environment to focus on your ideas. Add annotations to any canvas; assign each wireframe a unique URL that you can bookmark or share.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">There are two templates to choose from: a browser window or a mobile phone. The mobile version comes in vertical and landscape orientations, and every element of the wireframe can be edited or transformed.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">11.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wireframesketcher.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Wireframe Sketcher</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Wireframesketcher\" src=\"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxLzIxL3dpcmVmcmFtZXNrLjQ2NjJlLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTg1MHg1OTA-CmUJanBn/47a4a4f1/0e7/wireframesketcher.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">A powerful, flexible tool to quickly create wireframes, mockups and prototypes for desktop and mobile applications, Wireframe Sketcher is available both as a standalone application or as a plugin for any Eclipse IDE. It has a rough, hand-drawn look so you won\'t be distracted by little details. It boasts an extensive set of UI controls, with flexible controls that can be customized. The speed-optimized interface, multiple shortcuts, grid snapping and smart guides make it a fast and efficient choice. Prototypes can be linked and exported as clickable PDFs.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">The&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wireframesketcher.com/mockups/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Mockups Gallery</a>&nbsp;stores extra widgets, stencils, icons and templates to download and use in your own projects, including stencils for Android, iPhone, iPad and Windows mobiles.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">12.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.omnigroup.com/products/omnigraffle/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Omnigraffle</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Omnigraffle\" src=\"http://rack.3.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxLzM3L29tbmlncmFmZmxlLjMwNjk4LmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTg1MHg1OTA-CmUJanBn/207bc12a/fa7/omnigraffle.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Omnigraffle is powerful wireframe and diagram application with a vast library of stencils to quickly mock up an iPhone app. Using the Pen Tool you can even create your own set of custom shapes or stencils. Layers are used to organize your project within the canvas -- if you\'re familiar with Adobe Photoshop or Illustrator, this will be familiar territory. Shared layers are especially useful for common elements, as they can be re-used across multiple canvases. As Omnigraffle is also a design tool, it includes features such as leading, kerning and margins.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">It comes packed with a variety of templates and stencils, with others available from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.graffletopia.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Graffletopia</a>, including iPhone, iPad and Android stencils.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">13.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://pidoco.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Pidoco</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Pidoco\" src=\"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxLzAxL3BpZG9jby4xZDI1Yy5qcGcKcAl0aHVtYgk4NTB4NTkwPgplCWpwZw/5421f083/0b4/pidoco.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Pidoco is a web-based prototyping app for rapidly creating clickable wireframes and UI prototypes. It features smart sharing and collaboration features, with a convenient usability testing module. With a variety of mobile UI elements, you can quickly create prototypes for mobile apps using the drag and drop interface, or make use of the mobile page templates to save time. You can choose between the \"plain\" or \"sketched\" modes to display wireframes and from a large library of pre-fabricated UI elements to quickly create professional wireframes.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">You can simulate and test interactive prototypes directly on mobile devices, like an iPad or iPhone, without any downloads or installation.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">14.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.flairbuilder.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Flair Builder</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Flairbuilder\" src=\"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxL2VhL2ZsYWlyYnVpbGRlLmViZjNmLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTg1MHg1OTA-CmUJanBn/78ff70d4/683/flairbuilder.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">A prototyping tool for creating interactive wireframes, FlairBuilder lets you start with low-fidelity sketches and jump to a higher-fidelity wireframe with a single click. There is a large set of built-in widgets and components (over 70), plus an extensive stencils library.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">It\'s quick and easy to preview your project and you can export a fully functional HTML prototype. The advanced interactions are of interest, as you can combine several to create complex behaviors, from hover effects to links and transitions. Wireframes are organized in a natural, tree-like structure. FlairBuilder can read your wireframe structure and generate a site map to easily view page hierarchy.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Basic iPhone support is built in, with stencils available for advanced iOS and Android support. You can export prototypes to HTML to allow testing on real mobile devices.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">15.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://iphonemockup.lkmc.ch/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">iPhone Mockup</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Iphonemockup\" src=\"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxL2EzL2lwaG9uZW1vY2t1LjliNGI5LmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTg1MHg1OTA-CmUJanBn/4c859864/855/iphonemockup.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">An incredibly simple web app, iPhone Mockup allows you to create, well, iPhone app mockups and share them with others. Any changes made are synced to everyone who has the project\'s URL, and they can also make live edits.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">The app is currently in alpha. It\'s important to note there is no password protection, so anyone with the appropriate URL can access and view your mockups. There are two styles of wireframing offered -- illustration and pencil&nbsp;<br>-- and you can switch styles at any point using the style selector.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">The variety of components is limited, however, there are enough to create a basic wireframe, with the ability to upload images and change text labels. The app is designed to work on Firefox, Safari, Chrome and Internet Explorer 8 and above.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">16.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.hotgloo.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">HotGloo</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Hotgloo\" src=\"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxLzQyL2hvdGdsb28uOWJhNjkuanBnCnAJdGh1bWIJODUweDU5MD4KZQlqcGc/0ee068dc/3ce/hotgloo.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">HotGloo is a rich web app that is incredibly flexible with virtually every UI element needed to design wireframes and prototypes. It recently added dedicated iPad and iPhone stencil kits, which include all the standard interface components: labels, tabs, icons, maps, buttons and a variety of different table views.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">The contextual menus allow for a great amount of control over how an element appears and include support for CSS3 effects. The lightweight but powerful template system is impressive -- double-click and edit template components on the canvas -- with an overall emphasis on responsive interactivity built into the app.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">The collaborative features mean more than one member of your team can work on a wireframe at the same time, and you can invite others to view and provide feedback on the project. There is even a built-in chat function to discuss the wireframe in real time.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">17.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.invisionapp.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Invision</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Invision\" src=\"http://rack.0.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxLzA3L2ludmlzaW9uLmI1MGNhLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTg1MHg1OTA-CmUJanBn/0fedec01/e17/invision.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">While not strictly for mobile wireframing, InvisionApp provides a rapid prototyping environment that can quickly link up your UX/UI sketches, digital wireframes and even high-fidelity designs to test how your mobile app works and share with the rest of your team.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">If you prefer to sketch your layouts first, this could be a great choice, as you can use your normal process and design tools, upload your screen (as JPEGs or PNGs), then link them up to create a functional prototype. Using hotspots to click around the screens, you can create a realistic experience of the interactions. You can leave comments and feedback on each project, either public or private, and mark each discussion read or complete once it\'s been viewed and dealt with.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Invision adds some lovely touches when working with iOS, including a custom home screen icon and custom loading screen. And by adding the project to your home screen from Safari, you can completely remove all browser chrome.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">18.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://mokk.me/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Mokk.me</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Mokkme\" src=\"http://rack.3.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxLzU4L21va2ttZS5kNTgwMS5qcGcKcAl0aHVtYgk4NTB4NTkwPgplCWpwZw/b6ac6692/7d2/mokkme.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">A quick, mobile mockup creator with a simple drag-and-drop interface, Mokk.me creates an app you can share, test on multiple platforms and use in production, without knowing a single line of code. It is currently in beta, so expect bugs, however, it is a quick, rudimentary method that can be used by just about anyone to create a layout of his proposed app. You can drag, drop and edit widgets, build and link pages and choose transition animations. It features pages and buttons, image widgets, text input and checkbox forms.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Interestingly, the HTML, CSS and JavaScript can be reused later to facilitate the final production of the app. Once you\'ve created your mockup, you can share and test it on iOS and Android.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">19.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://iplotz.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">iPlotz</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Iplotz\" src=\"http://rack.0.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxLzA3L2lwbG90ei5kNjE5My5qcGcKcAl0aHVtYgk4NTB4NTkwPgplCWpwZw/fceb72c0/c21/iplotz.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Create clickable, navigable mockups and wireframes for both websites and mobile applications. You can drag and drop components onto a resizable page, link them or add hotspot links to other screens or pages and upload your own images. You can choose between iPhone/iPad and Android templates, each with a unique set of components, to build a fully functional prototype. The interface is cleverly organized and allows for collaboration with shareable editing rights, task management and a comment system.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Projects can be exported as IPML, JPG, PNG, PDF or HTML, or enabled as a preview URL, which can be emailed to project members.</p></div></div></li><li class=\"slide\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><div class=\"meta\"><h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 2.45rem; line-height: 1.2; clear: left;\">20.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://pencil.evolus.vn/Default.html\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">Pencil Project</a></h2></div><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\"><img alt=\"Pencil\" src=\"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA0LzAxL2E4L3BlbmNpbC5hZjI2Yy5qcGcKcAl0aHVtYgk4NTB4NTkwPgplCWpwZw/9d398f1d/922/pencil.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 950px;\"></figure><div class=\"meta\"><div class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Pencil is an open-source tool for making diagrams and GUI prototyping, available as either a&nbsp;<a href=\"http://pencil.evolus.vn/Downloads.html\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">standalone application</a>&nbsp;or a Firefox extension. It provides a built-in shapes collection for drawing various types of user interfaces, including flowchart elements, UI and general purpose shapes, for use in both desktop and mobile interfaces.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.75em;\">Individually link elements to a specific page in a document, then convert them to HTML hyperlinks when exported into web format.&nbsp;<br>You\'ll find a variety of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://pencil.evolus.vn/Stencils-Templates.html\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">mobile stencils</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/evoluspencil/downloads/list?q=label:Stencil\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(12, 116, 166); text-decoration: none;\">templates</a>&nbsp;to download and install as Pencil add-ons. These include an Android 4.0 shape collection, iOS wireframes, iOS GUI shapes and more.<span id=\"sceditor-end-marker\" class=\"sceditor-selection sceditor-ignore\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\"></span><span id=\"sceditor-start-marker\" class=\"sceditor-selection sceditor-ignore\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\"></span></p></div></div></li></ul>', 'quote', '', 'http://mashable.com/2013/04/02/wireframing-tools-mobile/#_', '', '100', 'en_SG', '', '4028d98139636d9d013963783d60007c', 'Gan Jianping', '2013-06-11 11:21:07', '2013-06-11 19:21:07', '0');
INSERT INTO `cm_article` VALUES ('8a3321b63f26cfbb013f6458f8e402be', '', 'Project Requirement', 'Website, Mobile app', '<p>Categories,&nbsp;New Posts, Archives, Who\'s Online, Tags,&nbsp;Most Viewed, Top Downloads<span id=\"sceditor-end-marker\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\" class=\"sceditor-selection sceditor-ignore\"></span><span id=\"sceditor-start-marker\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\" class=\"sceditor-selection sceditor-ignore\"></span></p>', '', '', '', '', '100', 'en_SG', '', '4028d98139636d9d013963783d60007c', 'Gan Jianping', '2013-06-21 01:28:39', '2013-06-22 07:48:25', '0');
INSERT INTO `cm_article` VALUES ('8a3321b63f26cfbb013fb6faf17104ef', '', 'Objective-C 基础', '内存管理：堆（alloc,全局变量和初始化数据），栈（局部变量），数据区（静态变量和字符常量），代码区. 一个变量都是有两块内存，一个堆内存，一个栈内存，一般都是一个栈内存指向一块堆内存', '<p><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \"><div><b><span id=\"sceditor-start-marker\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none; \" class=\"sceditor-selection sceditor-ignore\"></span>内存管理</b>：堆（alloc,全局变量和初始化数据），栈（局部变量），数据区（静态变量和字符常量），代码区.&nbsp;一个变量都是有两块内存，一个堆内存，一个栈内存，一般都是一个栈内存指向一块堆内存<span id=\"sceditor-end-marker\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none; \" class=\"sceditor-selection sceditor-ignore\"></span></div><div><div><b>引用计数</b>（retainCount）表示对象有几个人在使用它；对象被创建时alloc 引用计数加1，当发送retain消息时，引用计数加1；当release消息时，减1；当对象的引用计数为0时，系统自动调用dealloc方法销毁该对象；</div><div><b>对象所有权</b>：计数器变化,&nbsp;创建或复制某对象，没有创建而是保留对象使用，copy，+1， &nbsp;autorelease &nbsp;，-1&nbsp;</div><div><b>assign</b>&nbsp;：直接赋直，默认，只是一个别名作用, &nbsp;<b>retain</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;保留对象，两个对象指向同一个位置,&nbsp;<b>copy</b>&nbsp;拷贝对象，开辟一个新内存空间，分别指向不同的内存位置</div><div><b>自动释放池</b>（Autorelease pool）是可以存放一些实体的集合，在自动释放池中的对象，是能够被自动释放的 nsobject 类提供了一个autorelease消息，当我们向一个对象发送autorelease消息时，这个对象就被放入了自动释放池，对象a retain对象b，对象b retain对象a，这时两个对象a和b都没有办法得到释放，这种情况我们称之为循环饮用</div></div><div><b>Foundation</b>框架主要定义了一些基础类，基于NSObject；NS前缀是cocoa的来源NextSTEP简写；</div><div><b>基本数据类型</b>转化封装为对象才能发送消息;&nbsp;对象类型初始化都分为实例方法和类方法</div><div><div><div><b>id</b>声明的类型为动态类型，动态绑定：程序只有在运行时才能确定对象调用的实际方法</div><div><b>数组</b>不能存放基本数据类型，只能封装好存放类的对象</div><div><b>字典对象</b>的键值不可以为空，如果需要表示空值，则使用<font face=\"Noteworthy\">NSNull对象</font>表示</div><div><span style=\"line-height: 26px; text-align: left; \"><font face=\"Noteworthy\">NSSet集合类是一组单值对象的集合，元素无序，但对象唯一，集合类和数组类用法相似</font></span></div><div><p><br></p></div><div><div>[ NSString alloc ] initwithString @“ ” ] &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; // 常量区</div><div>[ NSString alloc ] initwithFormat：@“”, x] &nbsp;//堆区</div><div>不可变字符串：两者内容相同，但是指针不同，如果在常量区的两个常量相等，则指针也相等。堆内存区是另外开辟内存的。如果是可变字符串MutableNSString，则全部都是在堆区；</div></div><div><div>@<b>try</b>&nbsp;{ &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; [box setNumber:-10]; &nbsp;</div><div>} &nbsp;</div><div>@<b>catch</b>&nbsp;(<b>NSException</b>&nbsp;*exception) { &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; NSLog(@\"%@\",[exception name]); &nbsp;</div><div>} &nbsp;</div><div>@<b>finally</b>&nbsp;{ &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; [box printNumber]; &nbsp;</div><div>}</div></div><div><br></div><div><div>NSLog输出格式：&nbsp;<b>%@</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;对象 &nbsp;&nbsp;<b>%d, %i</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;整数 &nbsp;<b>%u</b>&nbsp;无符整形 &nbsp;<b>%f</b>&nbsp; 浮点/双字 &nbsp;<b>%x, %X</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;二进制整数 &nbsp;<b>%o</b>&nbsp;八进制整数 &nbsp;<b>%zu&nbsp;</b>size_t &nbsp;<b>%p&nbsp;</b>指针&nbsp;<b>%e</b>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;浮点/双字 （科学计算）&nbsp;<b>%g&nbsp;</b>浮点/双字 &nbsp;<b>%s</b>&nbsp;C 字符串 &nbsp;<b>%.*s&nbsp;</b>Pascal字符串&nbsp;<b>%c&nbsp;</b>字符&nbsp;<b>%C</b>&nbsp;unichar&nbsp;<b>%lld&nbsp;</b>64位长整数 &nbsp;<b>%llu&nbsp;</b>无符64位长整数 &nbsp;<b>%Lf</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;64位双字</div><div><br></div><div style=\"font-size: 19px; \"><b>字符串(NSString)常用方法 :&nbsp;</b></div><div><p><b>NSString</b>&nbsp;*string = [string &nbsp;<b>uppercaseString</b>&nbsp;]&nbsp; //&nbsp; 全部大写 &nbsp; &nbsp;</p><p>[string&nbsp;<b>capitalizedString</b>] &nbsp;//首字母大写，其他小写</p><p></p><p>NSArray *array=[string&nbsp;<b>componentsSeparatedByString</b>:@\" \"]&nbsp; // 将字符串通过分隔号分开成数组 (@“ a b c”)</p><p></p><p>string&nbsp;<b>substringToIndex</b>：1]&nbsp;&nbsp; //从开头截取到指定位置，但不包含该位置</p><p>[string&nbsp;<b>substringFromIndex</b>：1 ]&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; //从指定位置开始 截取之后的全部字符串，包含该位置</p><p><b>NSRange</b>&nbsp;range={1,2 } //&nbsp; range.location=1, range.length=2&nbsp;&nbsp; // 截取的索引位置和截取的长度</p><p>[string&nbsp;<b>substringWithRange</b>：range]&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; //&nbsp; 截取范围（索引，长度）</p><p>[string&nbsp;<b>stringByAppendingString</b>：str2]&nbsp; //&nbsp; 字符串拼接</p><p>NSRange range=[ string&nbsp;<b>rangeOfString</b>：string2]； //string里面是否包含string2</p><p>range.location!=&nbsp;<b>NSNotFound</b>&nbsp;&nbsp; //&nbsp;&nbsp; 查询字符串对象</p><p>[string1 insertString：string2&nbsp;<b>atIndex</b>：1 ]&nbsp; //&nbsp; 在可变字符串中插入字符串</p><p>[string1&nbsp;<b>deleteCharactersInRange</b>：NSMakeRange（1，2）]&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; // 在可变字符串中删除字符 &nbsp;</p><p>[string1&nbsp;<b>replaceCharactersInRange</b>：NSMakeRange（1，2）withString：string2]&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; //&nbsp; 替换字符串</p><p><br></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; \"><b>数组(NSArray)常用方法</b></p><p></p><p>[array&nbsp;<b>arrayByAddingObject</b>：string]&nbsp;&nbsp; //&nbsp;增加一个对象</p><p>string1 = [array&nbsp;<b>componentsJoinedBySyring</b>：@“，”]&nbsp; // 用指定的字符串将数组中的元素连接起来 成另外一个字符串</p><p><b>Bool</b>&nbsp; isContain=[array&nbsp;<b>containsObject</b>：string]&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; //&nbsp; 是否包含某对象</p><p>[array&nbsp;<b>indexOfObject</b>：string]&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 查找该对象的索引</p><p>[NSMutableArray&nbsp;<b>arrayWithCapacity</b>：5]&nbsp;&nbsp; //初始化可变数组&nbsp; 设定元素个数为5，但可以更改元素个数，期望值</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div><br></div></div><div style=\"font-size: 18px; \"><b>字典(NSDictionary)常用方法</b></div><div><div>[ NSDictionary &nbsp;<b>dicionaryWithContentsOfFile</b>：path] &nbsp;// 以文件内容初始化字典，一般是plist文件或者xml文件，也可以通过相同方式初始化数组</div><div><b>NSEnumerator</b>&nbsp;*enumerator = [dic&nbsp;<b>keyEnumerator</b>] &nbsp;// 枚举字典的key转化为一个枚举对象</div><div><b>id&nbsp;</b>key=[enumerator&nbsp;<b>nextObject</b>] &nbsp;// &nbsp;枚举下一个对象</div><div>[dic&nbsp;<b>allKeys</b>] &nbsp; &nbsp;// 字典的所有键</div><div>[dic&nbsp;<b>allValues</b>] &nbsp; // 字典的所有值</div><div>[dic2&nbsp;<b>addEntriesFromDictionar</b>y：dic3] &nbsp; // 向字典对象2中添加整个字典对象3</div></div><div><br></div><div style=\"font-size: 18px; \"><b>集合(NSSet)常用方法</b></div><div><p>[ set4 intersectsSet：set2]&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; //&nbsp; 集合4和集合2是否存在相同元素，即是否存在交集</p><p>[ set4 intersectSet：set2]&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; // 交集，取相同元素</p><p>[ set4 isSubsetOfSet：set2]&nbsp; // 集合4是否为集合2的子集合&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 包含关系</p><p>[ set4 munusSet：set2]&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; //&nbsp; 集合4减去集合2中的元素，即减去集合2中相同的元素&nbsp; 等于集合4剩下的元素</p><p>[ set4 unionSet：set2]&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; // 并集</p></div><div><br></div></div></div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 19px; \"><b>系统应用常用方法</b></div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \">float&nbsp;scale = [[UIScreenmainScreen]&nbsp;scale];//得到设备的分辨率</div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \"><p>scale = 1; 的时候是代表当前设备是320*480的分辨率（就是iphone4之前的设备，一般模拟器）<br></p><p>scale = 2; 的时候是代表分辨率为640*960的分辨率（retina显示屏）</p><div><br></div></div></p>', '', '', '', '', '100', 'zh_CN', '', '4028d98139636d9d013963783d60007c', 'Gan Jianping', '2013-07-07 02:34:26', '2013-07-07 10:34:26', '0');
INSERT INTO `cm_article` VALUES ('8a3321b63f26cfbb013fb6fc004704fe', '', 'Objective-C 类', 'ios只能单继承，通过协议的方式实现多继承特点. 实例变量还只是声明内存为空，alloc之后才分配内存创建对象，init后才能使用；', '<p><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \"><div>ios只能<b>单继承</b>，通过协议的方式实现多继承特点.</div><div><div><span id=\"sceditor-start-marker\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none; \" class=\"sceditor-selection sceditor-ignore\"></span>实例变量还只是声明内存为空，<b>alloc</b>之后才分配内存创建对象，<b>init</b>后才能使用；<span id=\"sceditor-end-marker\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none; \" class=\"sceditor-selection sceditor-ignore\"></span></div><div>同一个类的每个对象有不同的实例变量的存储空间；</div><div>同一个类的不同对象放在栈区，一个对象的不同实例变量放在堆区</div><div>在init方法中，需调用super init方法初始化父类在赋值给本类，为了防止父类在初始化过程中返回的对象不同于原先创建的对象</div><div><p><b>设置器</b>&nbsp;set方法，<b>访问器</b>&nbsp;get方法，get方法前面不要加get，因为get在oc里面是关键字，一般是通过返回值设置get方法，用@property简化设置器和访问器，@property声明set和get方法，@synthesize实现set和get方法,在@property和@synthesize简化get和set方法后，就能通过点语法来获取实例变量</p><p></p><p>在<b>@property</b>（）中 可以填写的属性&nbsp;<b>readwrite</b>&nbsp;：默认,&nbsp;<b>readonly</b>&nbsp; 只读，意味着没有set方法，只有get方法,&nbsp;<b>assign</b>&nbsp;：默认，引用计数不增加，用于基本数据类型int等，非指针类型,&nbsp;<b>retain</b>&nbsp; 引用计数增加,&nbsp;原子性：<b>actomic</b>&nbsp; 默认；是oc中一种线程保护技术，是防止在未完成的时候被另外一个线程使用，造成数据错误;&nbsp;非原子性：<b>nonatomic</b></p><p></p></div><div><br></div><div style=\"font-size: 19px; \"><b>类的定义</b></div><div><h4 style=\"line-height: 26px; text-align: left; \"><font face=\"Noteworthy\">1 在头文件里添加类成员变量和方法</font></h4></div><div><div>@<b>interface</b>&nbsp;Worker :&nbsp;<b>NSObject</b>&nbsp; //继承NSObject</div><div>{ &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; NSString *name; &nbsp;//<b>protected</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div>@<b>private</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; int age; &nbsp;</div><div>@<b>protected</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; float wage; &nbsp;</div><div>@<b>public</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; id boss; &nbsp;</div><div>}&nbsp;</div></div><div>-(<b>Worker*</b>) initWithNameAndAge:(NSString*) aName setAge:(NSInteger) aAge //自定义构造函数</div><div><div>-(void) setName: (NSString*) name; //类方法用+号开始，实例化方法用 -号开始</div><div>-(void)&nbsp;setNameAndAge<b>:(NSString*)</b>&nbsp;aName&nbsp;<b>setAge:(NSInteger)</b>&nbsp;aAge; //使用多个参数</div><div>-(NSString*) Name; &nbsp;//等于getName</div><div>@<b>end&nbsp;</b></div><div><br></div><div><b>2实现类中的方法</b></div></div><div><div>@<b>implementation&nbsp;</b>Worker</div><div><div>-(Student*) initWithNameAndAge:(NSString*) aName setAge:(NSInteger) aAge &nbsp;</div><div>{ &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; self = [super init]; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; if ( self ) { &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; [self setNameAndAge:aName setAge:aAge]; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; } &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; return self; &nbsp;</div><div>} &nbsp;</div></div><div><div>-(void) setNameAndAge:(NSString*) aName setAge:(NSInteger) aAge &nbsp;</div><div>{ &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; name = aName; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; age = aAge; &nbsp;</div><div>}&nbsp;</div></div><div>@<b>end&nbsp;</b></div></div><div><b>3&nbsp;创建类对象，调用方法</b></div><div>Worker *worker = [[Worker alloc]<b>init</b>]; &nbsp;</div><div>Worker&nbsp;*student&nbsp;=&nbsp;[[Worker alloc]<b>initWithNameAndAge</b>:@\"ganjp\"&nbsp;setAge:30]; &nbsp;</div><div>[student setNameAndAge:@\"李四\" setAge:20];&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><b>类目/类别（Category）</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;为封装类添加额外的方法，对<b>现有类扩展</b>. 无法向类目中添加新的<b>实例变量</b>, 类目方法更高的优先级，因此一般不要覆盖<b>现有类方法,&nbsp;</b>类目不继承原始类，只兼容和扩展原始类, 子类可以继承已经添加类目的父类的所有方</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<b>在NSString 上增加一个方法来判断它是否是有效的 URL</b>&nbsp;:&nbsp;if&nbsp;([str1&nbsp;isURL])&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; @<b>interface</b>&nbsp;NSString&nbsp;(extension) &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- (BOOL)&nbsp;isURL; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;@end&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;@<b>implementation</b>&nbsp;NSString(extension) &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- (BOOL) isURL{ &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;if( [self hasPrefix:@\"http://\"] ) &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;return YES; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;else &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;return NO; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;} &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;@end&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div><div><b>扩展/延展（Extension）</b></div><div>又称“匿名”的类目，主要用来定义类的<b>私有方法</b>，一般是<b>在类的实现文件</b>@implementation之上定义如：<b>Person（）</b>&nbsp;和类目的区别在于括号里面是空的，没有名字的，暂时性的存在，<b>只能本类调用方法</b>，子类也无法调用父类的延展，在本类的实现文件@implementation之上也可以定义私有方法，私有的静态变量</div><div><p></p><p>@<b>interface</b>&nbsp;JpViewController ()</p><p>@property&nbsp;(weak,&nbsp;nonatomic)&nbsp;IBOutlet&nbsp;UITextField&nbsp;*userNameTf;</p><p>- (IBAction)login:(id)sender;</p><p>@<b>end</b></p><p></p><p><br></p></div></div><div><b>协议（Protocol）</b></div><div><p>没有父类也不能定义实例变量，只声明方法，声明未知类的接口，两个类之间的通信，@required ：必须实现。默认；@optional ：选择性的实现；</p><p>NSObject为基本类根类也为基协议，可以写也可以不写</p></div><div><b>代理设计模式（Delegate）</b></div><div><p>两个对象协同解决难题，用于对象之间的通信,&nbsp;一般用于控件和控制器对象之间的通信，控件事件发生要通过控制器行为表现,&nbsp;就是说该对象类有委托方法，实现委托方法（遵守委托协议）需要在其他类中实现，通过其他类对象来代理解决.</p></div><div>A view 里面包含了B view,&nbsp;b view需要修改a view界面</div><div><div><b>B_View.h</b>: &nbsp;</div><div>@<b>protocol</b>&nbsp;UIBViewDelegate &lt;NSObject&gt;&nbsp;</div><div>@optional &nbsp;</div><div>- (void)ontouch:(UIScrollView *)scrollView; //声明协议方法 &nbsp;</div><div>@<b>end</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>@<b>interface</b>&nbsp;BView : UIScrollView&lt;UIScrollViewDelegate&gt; &nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div>{ &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;id&lt; UIBViewDelegate &gt;&nbsp;<b>_touchdelegate</b>; //设置委托变量 &nbsp;</div><div>} &nbsp;</div><div>@property(nonatomic,assign) id&lt; UIBViewDelegate &gt;&nbsp;<b>_touchdelegate</b>; &nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div>@<b>end</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><b>B_View.mm</b>: &nbsp;</div><div>@<b>synthesize</b>&nbsp;_touchdelegate; &nbsp;</div><div>- (id)initWithFrame:(CGRect)frame { &nbsp;</div><div>if (self = [super initWithFrame:frame]) {</div><div>&nbsp;<b>_touchdelegate</b>=nil; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;} &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;return self; &nbsp;</div><div>} &nbsp;</div><div>- (void) touchesBegan:(NSSet*)touches withEvent:(UIEvent*)event &nbsp;</div><div>{ &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;[super touchesBegan:touches withEvent:event]; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;if(_touchdelegate!=nil &amp;&amp; [_touchdelegate respondsToSelector: @selector(ontouch:) ] == true) &nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; [<b>_touchdelegate</b>&nbsp;ontouch:self]; &nbsp;//调用协议委托 &nbsp;</div><div>} &nbsp;</div><div>@end &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><b>A_View.h</b>: &nbsp;</div><div>@interface AViewController : UIViewController &lt;&nbsp;<b>UIBViewDelegate&nbsp;</b>&gt;&nbsp;</div><div>{ &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;BView *m_BView; &nbsp;</div><div>} &nbsp;</div><div>@end &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><b>A_View.mm</b>:&nbsp;</div><div>- (void)viewWillAppear:(BOOL)animated &nbsp;</div><div>{ &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;m_BView.<b>_touchdelegate</b>&nbsp;= self; //设置委托 &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;[self.view addSubview: m_BView]; &nbsp;</div><div>} &nbsp;</div><div>- (void)ontouch:(UIScrollView *)scrollView &nbsp;</div><div>{ &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; //实现协议 &nbsp;</div><div>}&nbsp;</div></div><div><br></div></div></div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \"><br></div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \">常用方法 ：</div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \"><div>-( BOOL)isKindOfClass:( Class)aClass; &nbsp; // 对象是否为aclass或其子类成员</div><div>-( BOOL)isMemberOfClass:( Class)aClass; &nbsp;//对象是否为aclass成员</div><div>-( BOOL)isSubclassOfClass:( Class)aClass; &nbsp;//对象是否为aclass的子类</div><div>-( BOOL)respondsToSelector:( SEL)aSelector ; &nbsp;//对象是否响应指定的方法</div></div></p>', '', '', '', '', '100', 'zh_CN', '', '4028d98139636d9d013963783d60007c', 'Gan Jianping', '2013-07-07 02:35:35', '2013-07-07 10:35:35', '0');
INSERT INTO `cm_article` VALUES ('8a3321b63f26cfbb013fb6fdeba60533', '', 'iOS Development', 'The UIKit Framework provides all the classes that app needs to construct and    manage its user interface.', '<p></p><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \">&nbsp; &nbsp; The&nbsp;<b>UIKit Framework</b>&nbsp;provides all the classes that app needs to construct and &nbsp;manage its user interface.</div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \">&nbsp; &nbsp; The call to&nbsp;<b>UIApplicationMain</b>&nbsp;creates an instance of the&nbsp;<b>UIApplication</b>&nbsp;class, an instance of the&nbsp;<b>app delegate</b>&nbsp;and scans the app\'s&nbsp;<b>Info.plist</b>&nbsp;file. The main job of the app delegate is to provide the window into which the app\'s content is drawn and can also perform some app configuration tasks before the app is displayed. The Info.plist file is an information property.</div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; In an iOS app, a&nbsp;<b>window</b>&nbsp;object provides a container for the app\'s visible content, helps deliver events to app objects, and helps the app respond to changes in the device\'s orientation. The window itself is invisible.</div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A&nbsp;<b>storyboard</b>&nbsp;contains an archive of the objects, transitions, and connections that define an app\'s user interface. When the app starts, Mainstoryboard.storyboard is loaded and the initial view controller is instantiated from it. A&nbsp;<b>view controller</b>&nbsp;is an object that manages an area of content; the&nbsp;<b>initial view controller</b>&nbsp;is simply the first view controller that gets loaded when an app starts. A view can contain other views. which are called subviews.</div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Storyboard View(Outline view, Canvas, Initial scene indicator, Scene, Scene dock), A&nbsp;<b>scene</b>&nbsp;represents a view controller, and a&nbsp;<b>segue</b>&nbsp;represents a transition between two scenes.</div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \">&nbsp; &nbsp; The outline view consists of the following items : (1)A&nbsp;<b>first responder</b>&nbsp;placeholder object. (2) A placeholder object named&nbsp;<b>Exit</b>&nbsp;for unwinding seques. (3) The JpViewController object. (4) A view.</div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<b>Add a TextField</b>&nbsp;: (1) select MainStoryboard.storyboard in the project navigator, then select View. (2)open the object library at the bottom of the utilities area. (3) drag a text field from the list at the object library and drop it onto the view. (4) with the text field still selected, open the Attributes inspector, make the following choices : Capitalization, Return Key. (5)Add an outlet of the text field : Control-drag form the text field in the view to the class extension in the implementation file. (6) Make the&nbsp;<b>Delegate Connection</b>&nbsp;: in the view, Control-drag from the text field to the yellow sphere in the scene dock, then select delegate in the Outlets section of the translucent panel. (7) select&nbsp;<b>ViewController.m</b>&nbsp;in the project navigator, then implement the&nbsp;<b>textFieldShouldReturn</b>&nbsp;method [textField&nbsp;<b>resignFirstResponder</b>]. (8)select ViewController.h, then to the end of the @interface line, add &lt;<b>UITextFieldDelegate</b>&gt;.&nbsp;</div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<b>Add a Button</b>&nbsp;:&nbsp;(1) drag a Button from the list at the object library and drop it onto the view.&nbsp; (2) Add an action for the button : on the canvas, Control-drag from the button to the class extension in ViewController.m.</div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \"><br></div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \">Resources :&nbsp;</div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \">&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.appcoda.com/use-storyboards-to-build-navigation-controller-and-table-view\">Use Storyboards to Build Navigation Controller and Table View</a></div><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Noteworthy-Light; font-size: 15px; \"><span id=\"sceditor-start-marker\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none; \" class=\"sceditor-selection sceditor-ignore\"></span><span id=\"sceditor-end-marker\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none; \" class=\"sceditor-selection sceditor-ignore\"></span><br></div><p></p>', '', '', '', '', '100', 'en_SG', '', '4028d98139636d9d013963783d60007c', 'Gan Jianping', '2013-07-07 02:37:41', '2013-08-26 13:11:11', '0');
